# Before submitting an issue, please fill this out

Is this a:
- [x] Issue with the OpenXml library
- [ ] Question on library usage

**Description**

When a `tableColumn` definition contains a `calculatedColumnFormula` that is an array formula (e.g. `<x:calculatedColumnFormula>{A2+A2}</x:calculatedColumnFormula>`) the resulting document (xlsx) is invalid but repairable.

**Information**

- .NET Target: .NET 6
- DocumentFormat.OpenXml Version: (2.16.0)
- ClosedXML (0.96.0)

**Repro**

```csharp
namespace ClosedXML.Excel.Tests
{
    using ClosedXML.Excel;
    using System.IO;

    internal class Program
    {
        private const string output_directory = "test_data";

        internal static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Directory.CreateDirectory(output_directory);

            not_working();
            working_v1();
            working_v2();

            //Array formulas in TableColumn.CalculatedColumnFormula generates invalid xlsx file
            static void not_working()
            {
                var (wb, ws) = create_base_document();

                ws.Cell(2, 2).FormulaA1 = "{Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]}";
                ws.Cell(3, 2).FormulaA1 = "{Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]}";

                using var not_working = File.Create(Path.Join(output_directory, "not_working.xlsx"));

                wb.SaveAs(not_working);
            }

            static void working_v1()
            {
                var (wb, ws) = create_base_document();

               //non-unique table formulas prevents addition of x:calculatedColumnFormula
                ws.Cell(2, 2).FormulaA1 = "{Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]}";
                ws.Cell(3, 2).FormulaA1 = "{Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]}";

                using var working_v1 = File.Create(Path.Join(output_directory, "working_v1.xlsx"));

                wb.SaveAs(working_v1);
            }

            //Normal formulas in TableColumn.CalculatedColumnFormula generates valid xlsx file
            static void working_v2()
            {
                var (wb, ws) = create_base_document();

                ws.Cell(2, 2).FormulaA1 = "Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]";
                ws.Cell(3, 2).FormulaA1 = "Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]+Table1[[#This Row],[Values]]";

                using var working_v2 = File.Create(Path.Join(output_directory, "working_v2.xlsx"));

                wb.SaveAs(working_v2, validate: true, evaluateFormulae: true);
            }

            static (IXLWorkbook, IXLWorksheet) create_base_document()
            {
                var wb = new XLWorkbook();
                var ws = wb.Worksheets.Add("Test data");

                ws.Cell(1, 1).Value = "Values";
                ws.Cell(1, 2).Value = "Sum";

                ws.Cell(2, 1).Value = 1;
                ws.Cell(3, 1).Value = 1;

                ws.Range("A1", "B3").CreateTable();

                return (wb, ws);
            }
        }
    }
}
``` 

**Observed**

Excel was able to open the file by repairing or removing the unreadable content.
*Removed Records: Table from /xl/tables/table1.xml part (Table)*

**Expected**

Document should be generated without errors

